p:
Normally, 
 Momordica spp. are consumed as vegetables and as nutrient supplements in Asia, Africa and South America and they are also used as medicinal herbs (
 Tan et al., 2008; 
 Madala et al., 2014; 
 Jia et al., 2017; 
 Islam and Jalaluddin, 2019). Different parts of 
 Momordica spp. are rich in both primary and secondary metabolites. The primary metabolites that are derived from 
 Momordica spp. include sugars, proteins and chlorophyll (
 Hassan and Umar, 2006; 
 Daniel et al., 2014), while secondary metabolites are alkaloids, flavonoids, tannins (
 Roškar and Lušin, 2012; 
 Mada et al., 2013; 
 Madala et al., 2016; 
 Mostafa et al., 2018). 
 Momordica spp. are good a source of phenolic compounds, gallic acid, gentisic acid (2,5-dihydroxyl benzoic acid), catechins, chlorogenic acid and epicatechin (
 Abegunde et al., 2018).
